3582    def _default_split_file(self, split_info: Dict) -> Optional[str]:
3583        """
3584        Generate a path to a split file from split parameters
3585        """
3586
3587        if split_info["partition_method"].startswith("time"):
3588            return None
3589        val_frac = split_info["val_frac"]
3590        test_frac = split_info["test_frac"]
3591        split_name = f'{split_info["partition_method"]}_val{val_frac * 100}%_test{test_frac * 100}%_len{split_info["len_segment"]}_overlap{split_info["overlap"]}'
3592        if not split_info["only_load_annotated"]:
3593            split_name += "_all"
3594        split_name += ".txt"
3595        return os.path.join(self.project_path, "results", "splits", split_name)
3596
3597    def _split_info_from_filename(self, split_name: str) -> Dict:
3598        """
3599        Get split parameters from default path to a split file
3600        """
3601
3602        if split_name is None:
3603            return {}
3604        try:
3605            name = os.path.basename(split_name)[:-4]
3606            split = name.split("_")
3607            if len(split) == 6:
3608                only_load_annotated = False
3609            else:
3610                only_load_annotated = True
3611            len_segment = int(split[3][3:])
3612            overlap = int(split[4][7:])
3613            method, val, test = split[:3]
3614            val = float(val[3:-1]) / 100
3615            test = float(test[4:-1]) / 100
3616            return {
3617                "partition_method": method,
3618                "val_frac": val,
3619                "test_frac": test,
3620                "only_load_annotated": only_load_annotated,
3621                "len_segment": len_segment,
3622                "overlap": overlap,
3623            }
3624        except:
3625            return {"partition_method": "file"}
3626
3627    def _fill(
3628        self,
3629        parameters: Dict,
3630        episode_name: str,
3631        load_experiment: str = None,
3632        load_epoch: int = None,
3633        load_strict: bool = True,
3634        only_load_model: bool = False,
3635        continuing: bool = False,
3636        enforce_split_parameters: bool = False,
3637    ) -> Dict:
3638        """
3639        Update the parameters from the config files with project specific information
3640
3641        Fill in the constant file path parameters and generate a unique log file and a model folder.
3642        Fill in the split file if the same split has been run before in the project and change partition method to
3643        from_file.
3644        Fill in saved data path if a dataset with the same data parameters already exists in the project.
3645        If load_experiment is not None, fill in the checkpoint path as well.
3646        The only_load_model training parameter is defined by the corresponding argument.
3647        If continuing is True, new files are not created and all information is loaded from load_experiment.
3648        If prediction is True, log and model files are not created.
3649        The enforce_split_parameters parameter is used to resolve conflicts
3650        between split file path and split parameters when they arise.
3651        """
3652
3653        pars = deepcopy(parameters)
3654        if episode_name == "_":
3655            self.remove_episode("_")
3656        log = os.path.join(self.project_path, "results", "logs", f"{episode_name}.txt")
3657        model_save_path = os.path.join(
3658            self.project_path, "results", "model", episode_name
3659        )
3660        if not continuing and (os.path.exists(log) or os.path.exists(model_save_path)):
3661            raise ValueError(
3662                f"The {episode_name} episode name is already in use! Set force=True to overwrite."
3663            )
3664        keys = ["val_frac", "test_frac", "partition_method"]
3665        if "len_segment" not in pars["general"] and "len_segment" in pars["data"]:
3666            pars["general"]["len_segment"] = pars["data"]["len_segment"]
3667        if "overlap" not in pars["general"] and "overlap" in pars["data"]:
3668            pars["general"]["overlap"] = pars["data"]["overlap"]
3669        if "len_segment" in pars["data"]:
3670            pars["data"].pop("len_segment")
3671        if "overlap" in pars["data"]:
3672            pars["data"].pop("overlap")
3673        split_info = {k: pars["training"][k] for k in keys}
3674        split_info["only_load_annotated"] = pars["general"]["only_load_annotated"]
3675        split_info["len_segment"] = pars["general"]["len_segment"]
3676        split_info["overlap"] = pars["general"]["overlap"]
3677        pars["training"]["log_file"] = log
3678        if not os.path.exists(model_save_path):
3679            os.mkdir(model_save_path)
3680        pars["training"]["model_save_path"] = model_save_path
3681        if load_experiment is not None:
3682            if load_experiment not in self._episodes().data.index:
3683                raise ValueError(f"The {load_experiment} episode does not exist!")
3684            old_episode = self._episode(load_experiment)
3685            old_file = old_episode.split_file()
3686            old_info = self._split_info_from_filename(old_file)
3687            if len(old_info) == 0:
3688                old_info = old_episode.split_info()
3689            if enforce_split_parameters:
3690                if split_info["partition_method"] != "file":
3691                    pars["training"]["split_path"] = self._default_split_file(
3692                        split_info
3693                    )
3694            else:
3695                equal = True
3696                if old_info["partition_method"] != split_info["partition_method"]:
3697                    equal = False
3698                if old_info["partition_method"] != "file":
3699                    if (
3700                        old_info["val_frac"] != split_info["val_frac"]
3701                        or old_info["test_frac"] != split_info["test_frac"]
3702                    ):
3703                        equal = False
3704                if not continuing and not equal:
3705                    warnings.warn(
3706                        f"The partitioning parameters in the loaded experiment ({old_info}) "
3707                        f"are not equal to the current partitioning parameters ({split_info}). "
3708                        f"The current parameters are replaced."
3709                    )
3710                pars["training"]["split_path"] = old_file
3711            pars["training"]["checkpoint_path"] = old_episode.model_file(load_epoch)
3712            pars["training"]["load_strict"] = load_strict
3713        else:
3714            pars["training"]["checkpoint_path"] = None
3715            if pars["training"]["partition_method"] == "file":
3716                if (
3717                    "split_path" not in pars["training"]
3718                    or pars["training"]["split_path"] is None
3719                ):
3720                    raise ValueError(
3721                        "The partition_method parameter is set to file but the "
3722                        "split_path parameter is not set!"
3723                    )
3724                elif not os.path.exists(pars["training"]["split_path"]):
3725                    raise ValueError(
3726                        f'The {pars["training"]["split_path"]} split file does not exist'
3727                    )
3728            else:
3729                pars["training"]["split_path"] = self._default_split_file(split_info)
3730        pars["training"]["only_load_model"] = only_load_model
3731        pars["data"]["saved_data_path"] = None
3732        pars["data"]["feature_save_path"] = None
3733        pars_data_copy = self._get_data_pars(pars)
3734        saved_data_name = self._saved_datasets().find_name(pars_data_copy)
3735        if saved_data_name is not None:
3736            pars["data"]["saved_data_path"] = self._dataset_store_path(saved_data_name)
3737            pars["data"]["feature_save_path"] = self._dataset_store_path(
3738                saved_data_name
3739            ).split(".")[0]
3740        else:
3741            dataset_path = self._dataset_store_path(episode_name)
3742            if os.path.exists(dataset_path):
3743                name, ext = dataset_path.split(".")
3744                i = 0
3745                while os.path.exists(f"{name}_{i}.{ext}"):
3746                    i += 1
3747                dataset_path = f"{name}_{i}.{ext}"
3748            pars["data"]["saved_data_path"] = dataset_path
3749            pars["data"]["feature_save_path"] = dataset_path.split(".")[0]
3750        split_split = pars["training"]["partition_method"].split(":")
3751        random = True
3752        for partition_method in options.partition_methods["fixed"]:
3753            method_split = partition_method.split(":")
3754            if len(split_split) != len(method_split):
3755                continue
3756            equal = True
3757            for x, y in zip(split_split, method_split):
3758                if y.startswith("{"):
3759                    continue
3760                if x != y:
3761                    equal = False
3762                    break
3763            if equal:
3764                random = False
3765                break
3766        if random and os.path.exists(pars["training"]["split_path"]):
3767            pars["training"]["partition_method"] = "file"
3768        pars["general"]["save_dataset"] = True
3769        return pars
3770
3771    def _get_data_pars(self, pars: Dict) -> Dict:
3772        """
3773        Get a complete description of the data from a general parameters dictionary
3774        """
3775
3776        pars_data_copy = deepcopy(pars["data"])
3777        for par in [
3778            "only_load_annotated",
3779            "exclusive",
3780            "feature_extraction",
3781            "ignored_clips",
3782            "len_segment",
3783            "overlap",
3784        ]:
3785            pars_data_copy[par] = pars["general"].get(par, None)
3786        pars_data_copy.update(pars["features"])
3787        return pars_data_copy
3788
3789    def count_classes(
3790        self,
3791        load_episode: str = None,
3792        parameters_update: Dict = None,
3793        remove_saved_features: bool = False,
3794        bouts: bool = True,
3795    ) -> Dict:
3796        """
3797        Get a dictionary of class counts in different modes
3798
3799        Parameters
3800        ----------
3801        load_episode : str, optional
3802            the episode settings to load
3803        parameters_update : dict, optional
3804            a dictionary of parameter updates (only for "data" and "general" categories)
3805        remove_saved_features : bool, default False
3806            if `True`, the dataset that is used for computation is then deleted
3807        bouts : bool, default False
3808            if `True`, instead of frame counts segment counts are returned
3809
3810        Returns
3811        -------
3812        class_counts : dict
3813            a dictionary where first-level keys are "train", "val" and "test", second-level keys are
3814            class names and values are class counts (in frames)
3815        """
3816
3817        if load_episode is None:
3818            task, parameters = self._make_task_training(
3819                episode_name="_", parameters_update=parameters_update, throwaway=True
3820            )
3821        else:
3822            task, parameters, _ = self._make_task_prediction(
3823                "_",
3824                load_episode=load_episode,
3825                parameters_update=parameters_update,
3826            )
3827        class_counts = task.count_classes(bouts=bouts)
3828        behaviors = task.behaviors_dict()
3829        class_counts = {
3830            kk: {behaviors.get(k, "unknown"): v for k, v in vv.items()}
3831            for kk, vv in class_counts.items()
3832        }
3833        if remove_saved_features:
3834            self._remove_stores(parameters)
3835        return class_counts
3836
3837    def plot_class_distribution(
3838        self,
3839        parameters_update: Dict = None,
3840        frame_cutoff: int = 1,
3841        bout_cutoff: int = 1,
3842        print_full: bool = False,
3843        remove_saved_features: bool = False,
3844    ) -> None:
3845        """
3846        Make a class distribution plot
3847
3848        You can either specify the parameters, choose an existing dataset or do neither (in that case a dataset
3849        is created or laoded for the computation with the default parameters).
3850
3851        Parameters
3852        ----------
3853        parameters_update : dict, optional
3854            a dictionary of parameter updates (only for "data" and "general" categories)
3855        remove_saved_features : bool, default False
3856            if `True`, the dataset that is used for computation is then deleted
3857        """
3858
3859        task, parameters = self._make_task_training(
3860            episode_name="_", parameters_update=parameters_update, throwaway=True
3861        )
3862        cutoff = {True: bout_cutoff, False: frame_cutoff}
3863        for bouts in [True, False]:
3864            class_counts = task.count_classes(bouts=bouts)
3865            if print_full:
3866                print("Bouts:" if bouts else "Frames:")
3867                for k, v in class_counts.items():
3868                    if sum(v.values()) != 0:
3869                        print(f"  {k}:")
3870                        values, keys = zip(
3871                            *[
3872                                x
3873                                for x in sorted(zip(v.values(), v.keys()), reverse=True)
3874                                if x[-1] != -100
3875                            ]
3876                        )
3877                        for kk, vv in zip(keys, values):
3878                            print(f"    {task.behaviors_dict()[kk]}: {vv}")
3879            class_counts = {
3880                kk: {k: v for k, v in vv.items() if v >= cutoff[bouts]}
3881                for kk, vv in class_counts.items()
3882            }
3883            for key, d in class_counts.items():
3884                if sum(d.values()) != 0:
3885                    values, keys = zip(
3886                        *[x for x in sorted(zip(d.values(), d.keys())) if x[-1] != -100]
3887                    )
3888                    keys = [task.behaviors_dict()[x] for x in keys]
3889                    plt.bar(keys, values)
3890                    plt.title(key)
3891                    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha="right")
3892                    if bouts:
3893                        plt.ylabel("bouts")
3894                    else:
3895                        plt.ylabel("frames")
3896                    plt.tight_layout()
3897                    plt.show()
3898        if remove_saved_features:
3899            self._remove_stores(parameters)
3900
3901    def _generate_mask(
3902        self,
3903        mask_name: str,
3904        perc_annotated: float = 0.1,
3905        parameters_update: Dict = None,
3906        remove_saved_features: bool = False,
3907    ) -> None:
3908        """
3909        Generate a real_lens for active learning simulation
3910
3911        Parameters
3912        ----------
3913        mask_name : str
3914            the name of the real_lens
3915        """
3916
3917        print(f"GENERATING {mask_name}")
3918        task, parameters = self._make_task_training(
3919            f"_{mask_name}", parameters_update=parameters_update, throwaway=True
3920        )
3921        val_intervals, val_ids = task.dataset("val").get_intervals()  # 1
3922        unannotated_intervals = task.dataset("train").get_unannotated_intervals()  # 2
3923        unannotated_intervals = task.dataset("val").get_unannotated_intervals(
3924            first_intervals=unannotated_intervals
3925        )
3926        ids = task.dataset("train").get_ids()
3927        mask = {video_id: {} for video_id in ids}
3928        total_all = 0
3929        total_masked = 0
3930        for video_id, clip_ids in ids.items():
3931            for clip_id in clip_ids:
3932                frames = np.ones(task.dataset("train").get_len(video_id, clip_id))
3933                if clip_id in val_intervals[video_id]:
3934                    for start, end in val_intervals[video_id][clip_id]:
3935                        frames[start:end] = 0
3936                if clip_id in unannotated_intervals[video_id]:
3937                    for start, end in unannotated_intervals[video_id][clip_id]:
3938                        frames[start:end] = 0
3939                annotated = np.where(frames)[0]
3940                total_all += len(annotated)
3941                masked = annotated[-int(len(annotated) * (1 - perc_annotated)) :]
3942                total_masked += len(masked)
3943                mask[video_id][clip_id] = self._get_intervals(masked)
3944        file = {
3945            "masked": mask,
3946            "val_intervals": val_intervals,
3947            "val_ids": val_ids,
3948            "unannotated": unannotated_intervals,
3949        }
3950        self._save_mask(file, mask_name)
3951        if remove_saved_features:
3952            self._remove_stores(parameters)
3953        print("\n")
3954        # print(f'Unmasked: {sum([(vv == 0).sum() for v in real_lens.values() for vv in v.values()])} frames')
3955
3956    def _get_intervals(self, frame_indices: np.ndarray):
3957        """
3958        Get a list of intervals from a list of frame indices
3959
3960        Example: `[0, 1, 2, 5, 6, 8] -> [[0, 3], [5, 7], [8, 9]]`.
3961
3962        Parameters
3963        ----------
3964        frame_indices : np.ndarray
3965            a list of frame indices
3966
3967        Returns
3968        -------
3969        intervals : list
3970            a list of interval boundaries
3971        """
3972
3973        masked_intervals = []
3974        if len(frame_indices) > 0:
3975            breaks = np.where(np.diff(frame_indices) != 1)[0]
3976            start = frame_indices[0]
3977            for k in breaks:
3978                masked_intervals.append([start, frame_indices[k] + 1])
3979                start = frame_indices[k + 1]
3980            masked_intervals.append([start, frame_indices[-1] + 1])
3981        return masked_intervals
3982
3983    def _update_mask_with_uncertainty(
3984        self,
3985        mask_name: str,
3986        episode_name: Union[str, None],
3987        classes: List,
3988        load_epoch: int = None,
3989        n_frames: int = 10000,
3990        method: str = "least_confidence",
3991        min_length: int = 30,
3992        augment_n: int = 0,
3993        parameters_update: Dict = None,
3994    ):
3995        """
3996        Update real_lens with frame-wise uncertainty scores for active learning
3997
3998        Parameters
3999        ----------
4000        mask_name : str
4001            the name of the real_lens
4002        episode_name : str
4003            the name of the episode to load
4004        classes : list
4005            a list of class names or indices; their uncertainty scores will be computed separately and stacked
4006        n_frames : int, default 10000
4007            the number of frames to "annotate"
4008        method : {"least_confidence", "entropy"}
4009            the method used to calculate the scores from the probability predictions (`"least_confidence"`: `1 - p_i` if
4010            `p_i > 0.5` or `p_i` if `p_i < 0.5`; `"entropy"`: `- p_i * log(p_i) - (1 - p_i) * log(1 - p_i)`)
4011        min_length : int
4012            the minimum length (in frames) of the annotated intervals
4013        augment_n : int, default 0
4014            the number of augmentations to average over
4015        parameters_update : dict, optional
4016            the dictionary used to update the parameters from the config
4017
4018        Returns
4019        -------
4020        score_dicts : dict
4021            a nested dictionary where first level keys are video ids, second level keys are clip ids and values
4022            are score tensors
4023        """
4024
4025        print(f"UPDATING {mask_name}")
4026        task, parameters, _ = self._make_task_prediction(
4027            prediction_name=mask_name,
4028            load_episode=episode_name,
4029            parameters_update=parameters_update,
4030            load_epoch=load_epoch,
4031            mode="train",
4032        )
4033        score_tensors = task.generate_uncertainty_score(classes, augment_n, method)
4034        self._update_mask(task, mask_name, score_tensors, n_frames, min_length)
4035        print("\n")
4036
4037    def _update_mask_with_BALD(
4038        self,
4039        mask_name: str,
4040        episode_name: str,
4041        classes: List,
4042        load_epoch: int = None,
4043        augment_n: int = 0,
4044        n_frames: int = 10000,
4045        num_models: int = 10,
4046        kernel_size: int = 11,
4047        min_length: int = 30,
4048        parameters_update: Dict = None,
4049    ):
4050        """
4051        Update real_lens with frame-wise Bayesian Active Learning by Disagreement scores for active learning
4052
4053        Parameters
4054        ----------
4055        mask_name : str
4056            the name of the real_lens
4057        episode_name : str
4058            the name of the episode to load
4059        classes : list
4060            a list of class names or indices; their uncertainty scores will be computed separately and stacked
4061        augment_n : int, default 0
4062            the number of augmentations to average over
4063        n_frames : int, default 10000
4064            the number of frames to "annotate"
4065        num_models : int, default 10
4066            the number of dropout masks to apply
4067        kernel_size : int, default 11
4068            the size of the smoothing gaussian kernel
4069        min_length : int
4070            the minimum length (in frames) of the annotated intervals
4071        parameters_update : dict, optional
4072            the dictionary used to update the parameters from the config
4073
4074        Returns
4075        -------
4076        score_dicts : dict
4077            a nested dictionary where first level keys are video ids, second level keys are clip ids and values
4078            are score tensors
4079        """
4080
4081        print(f"UPDATING {mask_name}")
4082        task, parameters, mode = self._make_task_prediction(
4083            mask_name,
4084            load_episode=episode_name,
4085            parameters_update=parameters_update,
4086            load_epoch=load_epoch,
4087        )
4088        score_tensors = task.generate_bald_score(
4089            classes, augment_n, num_models, kernel_size
4090        )
4091        self._update_mask(task, mask_name, score_tensors, n_frames, min_length)
4092        print("\n")
4093
4094    def _suggest_intervals(
4095        self,
4096        dataset: BehaviorDataset,
4097        score_tensors: Dict,
4098        n_frames: int,
4099        min_length: int,
4100    ) -> Dict:
4101        """
4102        Suggest intervals with highest score of total length `n_frames`
4103
4104        Parameters
4105        ----------
4106        dataset : BehaviorDataset
4107            the dataset
4108        score_tensors : dict
4109            a dictionary where keys are clip ids and values are framewise score tensors
4110        n_frames : int
4111            the number of frames to "annotate"
4112        min_length : int
4113
4114        Returns
4115        -------
4116        active_learning_intervals : Dict
4117            active learning dictionary with suggested intervals
4118        """
4119
4120        video_intervals, _ = dataset.get_intervals()
4121        taken = {
4122            video_id: defaultdict(lambda: {}) for video_id in video_intervals.keys()
4123        }
4124        annotated = dataset.get_annotated_intervals()
4125        for video_id in video_intervals:
4126            for clip_id in video_intervals[video_id]:
4127                taken[video_id][clip_id] = torch.zeros(
4128                    dataset.get_len(video_id, clip_id)
4129                )
4130                if video_id in annotated and clip_id in annotated[video_id]:
4131                    for start, end in annotated[video_id][clip_id]:
4132                        score_tensors[video_id][clip_id][:, start:end] = -10
4133                        taken[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 1
4134        n_frames = (
4135            sum([(vv == 1).sum() for v in taken.values() for vv in v.values()])
4136            + n_frames
4137        )
4138        factor = 1
4139        threshold_start = float(
4140            torch.mean(
4141                torch.tensor(
4142                    [
4143                        torch.mean(
4144                            torch.tensor([torch.mean(y[y > 0]) for y in x.values()])
4145                        )
4146                        for x in score_tensors.values()
4147                    ]
4148                )
4149            )
4150        )
4151        while (
4152            sum([(vv == 1).sum() for v in taken.values() for vv in v.values()])
4153            < n_frames
4154        ):
4155            threshold = threshold_start * factor
4156            intervals = []
4157            interval_scores = []
4158            key1 = list(score_tensors.keys())[0]
4159            key2 = list(score_tensors[key1].keys())[0]
4160            num_scores = score_tensors[key1][key2].shape[0]
4161            for i in range(num_scores):
4162                v_dict = dataset.find_valleys(
4163                    predicted=score_tensors,
4164                    threshold=threshold,
4165                    min_frames=min_length,
4166                    main_class=i,
4167                    low=False,
4168                )
4169                for v_id, interval_list in v_dict.items():
4170                    intervals += [x + [v_id] for x in interval_list]
4171                    interval_scores += [
4172                        float(torch.mean(score_tensors[v_id][clip_id][i, start:end]))
4173                        for start, end, clip_id in interval_list
4174                    ]
4175            intervals = np.array(intervals)[np.argsort(interval_scores)[::-1]]
4176            i = 0
4177            while sum(
4178                [(vv == 1).sum() for v in taken.values() for vv in v.values()]
4179            ) < n_frames and i < len(intervals):
4180                start, end, clip_id, video_id = intervals[i]
4181                i += 1
4182                taken[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 1
4183            factor *= 0.9
4184            if factor < 0.05:
4185                warnings.warn(f"Could not find enough frames!")
4186                break
4187        active_learning_intervals = {video_id: [] for video_id in video_intervals}
4188        for video_id in taken:
4189            for clip_id in taken[video_id]:
4190                if video_id in annotated and clip_id in annotated[video_id]:
4191                    for start, end in annotated[video_id][clip_id]:
4192                        taken[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 0
4193                if (taken[video_id][clip_id] == 1).sum() == 0:
4194                    continue
4195                indices = np.where(taken[video_id][clip_id].numpy())[0]
4196                boundaries = self._get_intervals(indices)
4197                active_learning_intervals[video_id] += [
4198                    [start, end, clip_id] for start, end in boundaries
4199                ]
4200        return active_learning_intervals
4201
4202    def _update_mask(
4203        self,
4204        task: TaskDispatcher,
4205        mask_name: str,
4206        score_tensors: Dict,
4207        n_frames: int,
4208        min_length: int,
4209    ) -> None:
4210        """
4211        Update the real_lens with intervals with the highest score of total length `n_frames`
4212
4213        Parameters
4214        ----------
4215        mask_name : str
4216            the name of the real_lens
4217        score_tensors : dict
4218            a dictionary where keys are clip ids and values are framewise score tensors
4219        n_frames : int
4220            the number of frames to "annotate"
4221        min_length : int
4222            the minimum length of the annotated intervals
4223        """
4224
4225        mask = self._load_mask(mask_name)
4226        video_intervals, _ = task.dataset("train").get_intervals()
4227        masked = {
4228            video_id: defaultdict(lambda: {}) for video_id in video_intervals.keys()
4229        }
4230        total_masked = 0
4231        total_all = 0
4232        for video_id in video_intervals:
4233            for clip_id in video_intervals[video_id]:
4234                masked[video_id][clip_id] = torch.zeros(
4235                    task.dataset("train").get_len(video_id, clip_id)
4236                )
4237                if (
4238                    video_id in mask["unannotated"]
4239                    and clip_id in mask["unannotated"][video_id]
4240                ):
4241                    for start, end in mask["unannotated"][video_id][clip_id]:
4242                        score_tensors[video_id][clip_id][:, start:end] = -10
4243                        masked[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 1
4244                if (
4245                    video_id in mask["val_intervals"]
4246                    and clip_id in mask["val_intervals"][video_id]
4247                ):
4248                    for start, end in mask["val_intervals"][video_id][clip_id]:
4249                        score_tensors[video_id][clip_id][:, start:end] = -10
4250                        masked[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 1
4251                total_all += torch.sum(masked[video_id][clip_id] == 0)
4252                if video_id in mask["masked"] and clip_id in mask["masked"][video_id]:
4253                    # print(f'{real_lens["masked"][video_id][clip_id]=}')
4254                    for start, end in mask["masked"][video_id][clip_id]:
4255                        masked[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 1
4256                        total_masked += end - start
4257        old_n_frames = sum(
4258            [(vv == 0).sum() for v in masked.values() for vv in v.values()]
4259        )
4260        n_frames = old_n_frames + n_frames
4261        factor = 1
4262        while (
4263            sum([(vv == 0).sum() for v in masked.values() for vv in v.values()])
4264            < n_frames
4265        ):
4266            threshold = float(
4267                torch.mean(
4268                    torch.tensor(
4269                        [
4270                            torch.mean(
4271                                torch.tensor([torch.mean(y[y > 0]) for y in x.values()])
4272                            )
4273                            for x in score_tensors.values()
4274                        ]
4275                    )
4276                )
4277            )
4278            threshold = threshold * factor
4279            intervals = []
4280            interval_scores = []
4281            key1 = list(score_tensors.keys())[0]
4282            key2 = list(score_tensors[key1].keys())[0]
4283            num_scores = score_tensors[key1][key2].shape[0]
4284            for i in range(num_scores):
4285                v_dict = task.dataset("train").find_valleys(
4286                    predicted=score_tensors,
4287                    threshold=threshold,
4288                    min_frames=min_length,
4289                    main_class=i,
4290                    low=False,
4291                )
4292                for v_id, interval_list in v_dict.items():
4293                    intervals += [x + [v_id] for x in interval_list]
4294                    interval_scores += [
4295                        float(torch.mean(score_tensors[v_id][clip_id][i, start:end]))
4296                        for start, end, clip_id in interval_list
4297                    ]
4298            intervals = np.array(intervals)[np.argsort(interval_scores)[::-1]]
4299            i = 0
4300            while sum(
4301                [(vv == 0).sum() for v in masked.values() for vv in v.values()]
4302            ) < n_frames and i < len(intervals):
4303                start, end, clip_id, video_id = intervals[i]
4304                i += 1
4305                masked[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 0
4306            factor *= 0.9
4307            if factor < 0.05:
4308                warnings.warn(f"Could not find enough frames!")
4309                break
4310        mask["masked"] = {video_id: {} for video_id in video_intervals}
4311        total_masked_new = 0
4312        for video_id in masked:
4313            for clip_id in masked[video_id]:
4314                if (
4315                    video_id in mask["unannotated"]
4316                    and clip_id in mask["unannotated"][video_id]
4317                ):
4318                    for start, end in mask["unannotated"][video_id][clip_id]:
4319                        masked[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 0
4320                if (
4321                    video_id in mask["val_intervals"]
4322                    and clip_id in mask["val_intervals"][video_id]
4323                ):
4324                    for start, end in mask["val_intervals"][video_id][clip_id]:
4325                        masked[video_id][clip_id][int(start) : int(end)] = 0
4326                indices = np.where(masked[video_id][clip_id].numpy())[0]
4327                mask["masked"][video_id][clip_id] = self._get_intervals(indices)
4328        for video_id in mask["masked"]:
4329            for clip_id in mask["masked"][video_id]:
4330                for start, end in mask["masked"][video_id][clip_id]:
4331                    total_masked_new += end - start
4332        self._save_mask(mask, mask_name)
4333        with open(
4334            os.path.join(self.project_path, "results", f"{mask_name}.txt"), "a"
4335        ) as f:
4336            f.write(f"from {total_masked} to {total_masked_new} / {total_all}" + "\n")
4337        print(f"Unmasked from {total_masked} to {total_masked_new} / {total_all}")
4338
4339    def plot_confusion_matrix(
4340        self,
4341        episode_name: str,
4342        load_epoch: int = None,
4343        parameters_update: Dict = None,
4344        type: str = "recall",
4345        mode: str = "val",
4346        remove_saved_features: bool = False,
4347    ) -> Tuple[ndarray, Iterable]:
4348        """
4349        Make a confusion matrix plot and return the data
4350
4351        If the annotation is non-exclusive, only false positive labels are considered.
4352
4353        Parameters
4354        ----------
4355        episode_name : str
4356            the name of the episode to load
4357        load_epoch : int, optional
4358            the index of the epoch to load (by default the last one is loaded)
4359        parameters_update : dict, optional
4360            a dictionary of parameter updates (only for "data" and "general" categories)
4361        mode : {'val', 'all', 'test', 'train'}
4362            the subset of the data to make the prediction for (forced to 'all' if data_path is not None)
4363        type : {"recall", "precision"}
4364            for datasets with non-exclusive annotation, if `type` is `"recall"`, only false positives are taken
4365            into account, and if `type` is `"precision"`, only false negatives
4366        remove_saved_features : bool, default False
4367            if `True`, the dataset that is used for computation is then deleted
4368
4369        Returns
4370        -------
4371        confusion_matrix : np.ndarray
4372            a confusion matrix of shape `(#classes, #classes)` where `A[i, j] = F_ij/N_i`, `F_ij` is the number of
4373            frames that have the i-th label in the ground truth and a false positive j-th label in the prediction,
4374            `N_i` is the number of frames that have the i-th label in the ground truth
4375        classes : list
4376            a list of labels
4377        """
4378
4379        task, parameters, mode = self._make_task_prediction(
4380            "_",
4381            load_episode=episode_name,
4382            load_epoch=load_epoch,
4383            parameters_update=parameters_update,
4384            mode=mode,
4385        )
4386        dataset = task.dataset(mode)
4387        prediction = task.predict(dataset, raw_output=True)
4388        confusion_matrix, classes, type = dataset.get_confusion_matrix(prediction, type)
4389        if remove_saved_features:
4390            self._remove_stores(parameters)
4391        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(len(classes), len(classes)))
4392        ax.imshow(confusion_matrix)
4393        # Show all ticks and label them with the respective list entries
4394        ax.set_xticks(np.arange(len(classes)))
4395        ax.set_xticklabels(classes)
4396        ax.set_yticks(np.arange(len(classes)))
4397        ax.set_yticklabels(classes)
4398        # Rotate the tick labels and set their alignment.
4399        plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right", rotation_mode="anchor")
4400        # Loop over data dimensions and create text annotations.
4401        for i in range(len(classes)):
4402            for j in range(len(classes)):
4403                ax.text(
4404                    j,
4405                    i,
4406                    np.round(confusion_matrix[i, j], 2),
4407                    ha="center",
4408                    va="center",
4409                    color="w",
4410                )
4411        if type is not None:
4412            ax.set_title(f"{type} {episode_name}")
4413        else:
4414            ax.set_title(episode_name)
4415        fig.tight_layout()
4416        plt.show()
4417        return confusion_matrix, classes

4571    def import_episodes(
4572        self,
4573        episodes_directory: str,
4574        name_map: Dict = None,
4575        repeat_policy: str = "error",
4576    ) -> None:
4577        """
4578        Import episodes exported with `Project.export_episodes`
4579
4580        Parameters
4581        ----------
4582        episodes_directory : str
4583            the path to the exported episodes directory
4584        name_map : dict
4585            a name change dictionary for the episodes: keys are old names, values are new names
4586        """
4587
4588        if name_map is None:
4589            name_map = {}
4590        episodes = pd.read_pickle(os.path.join(episodes_directory, "episodes.pickle"))
4591        to_remove = []
4592        import_string = "Imported episodes: "
4593        for episode_name in episodes.index:
4594            if episode_name in name_map:
4595                import_string += f"{episode_name} "
4596                episode_name = name_map[episode_name]
4597                import_string += f"({episode_name}), "
4598            else:
4599                import_string += f"{episode_name}, "
4600            try:
4601                self._check_episode_validity(episode_name, allow_doublecolon=True)
4602            except ValueError as e:
4603                if str(e).endswith("is already taken!"):
4604                    if repeat_policy == "skip":
4605                        to_remove.append(episode_name)
4606                    elif repeat_policy == "force":
4607                        self.remove_episode(episode_name)
4608                    elif repeat_policy == "error":
4609                        raise ValueError(
4610                            f"The {episode_name} episode name is already taken; please use the name_map parameter to rename it"
4611                        )
4612                    else:
4613                        raise ValueError(
4614                            f"The {repeat_policy} repeat policy is not recognized; please choose from ['skip', 'force' ans 'error']"
4615                        )
4616        episodes = episodes.drop(index=to_remove)
4617        self._episodes().update(
4618            episodes,
4619            name_map=name_map,
4620            force=(repeat_policy == "force"),
4621            data_path=self.data_path,
4622            annotation_path=self.annotation_path,
4623        )
4624        for episode_name in episodes.index:
4625            if episode_name in name_map:
4626                new_episode_name = name_map[episode_name]
4627            else:
4628                new_episode_name = episode_name
4629            model_dir = os.path.join(
4630                self.project_path, "results", "model", new_episode_name
4631            )
4632            old_model_dir = os.path.join(episodes_directory, "model", episode_name)
4633            if os.path.exists(model_dir):
4634                shutil.rmtree(model_dir)
4635            os.mkdir(model_dir)
4636            for file in os.listdir(old_model_dir):
4637                shutil.copyfile(
4638                    os.path.join(old_model_dir, file), os.path.join(model_dir, file)
4639                )
4640            log_file = os.path.join(
4641                self.project_path, "results", "logs", f"{new_episode_name}.txt"
4642            )
4643            old_log_file = os.path.join(
4644                episodes_directory, "logs", f"{episode_name}.txt"
4645            )
4646            shutil.copyfile(old_log_file, log_file)
4647        print(import_string)
4648        print("\n")
4649
4650    def export_episodes(
4651        self, episode_names: List, output_directory: str, name: str = None
4652    ) -> None:
4653        """
4654        Save selected episodes as a file that can be imported into another project with `Project.import_episodes`
4655
4656        Parameters
4657        ----------
4658        episode_names : list
4659            a list of string episode names
4660        output_directory : str
4661            the path to the directory where the episodes will be saved
4662        name : str, optional
4663            the name of the episodes directory (by default `exported_episodes`)
4664        """
4665
4666        if name is None:
4667            name = "exported_episodes"
4668        if os.path.exists(
4669            os.path.join(output_directory, name + ".zip")
4670        ) or os.path.exists(os.path.join(output_directory, name)):
4671            i = 1
4672            while os.path.exists(
4673                os.path.join(output_directory, name + f"_{i}.zip")
4674            ) or os.path.exists(os.path.join(output_directory, name + f"_{i}")):
4675                i += 1
4676            name = name + f"_{i}"
4677        dest_dir = os.path.join(output_directory, name)
4678        os.mkdir(dest_dir)
4679        os.mkdir(os.path.join(dest_dir, "model"))
4680        os.mkdir(os.path.join(dest_dir, "logs"))
4681        runs = []
4682        for episode in episode_names:
4683            runs += self._episodes().get_runs(episode)
4684        for run in runs:
4685            shutil.copytree(
4686                os.path.join(self.project_path, "results", "model", run),
4687                os.path.join(dest_dir, "model", run),
4688            )
4689            shutil.copyfile(
4690                os.path.join(self.project_path, "results", "logs", f"{run}.txt"),
4691                os.path.join(dest_dir, "logs", f"{run}.txt"),
4692            )
4693        data = self._episodes().get_subset(runs)
4694        data.to_pickle(os.path.join(dest_dir, "episodes.pickle"))

4696    def get_results_table(
4697        self,
4698        episode_names: List,
4699        metrics: List = None,
4700        include_std: bool = False,
4701        classes: List = None,
4702    ):
4703        """
4704        Genererate a `pandas` dataframe with a summary of episode results
4705
4706        Parameters
4707        ----------
4708        episode_names : list
4709            a list of names of episodes to include
4710        metrics : list, optional
4711            a list of metric names to include
4712        include_std : bool, default False
4713            if `True`, for episodes with multiple runs the mean and standard deviation will be displayed;
4714            otherwise only mean
4715        classes : list, optional
4716            a list of names of classes to include (by default all are included)
4717
4718        Returns
4719        -------
4720        results : pd.DataFrame
4721            a table with the results
4722        """
4723
4724        run_names = []
4725        for episode in episode_names:
4726            run_names += self._episodes().get_runs(episode)
4727        episodes = self.list_episodes(run_names, print_results=False)
4728        metric_columns = [x for x in episodes.columns if x[0] == "results"]
4729        results_df = pd.DataFrame()
4730        if metrics is not None:
4731            metric_columns = [
4732                x for x in metric_columns if x[1].split("_")[0] in metrics
4733            ]
4734        for episode in episode_names:
4735            results = []
4736            metric_set = set()
4737            for run in self._episodes().get_runs(episode):
4738                beh_dict = self.get_behavior_dictionary(run)
4739                res_dict = defaultdict(lambda: {})
4740                for column in metric_columns:
4741                    if np.isnan(episodes.loc[run, column]):
4742                        continue
4743                    split = column[1].split("_")
4744                    if split[-1].isnumeric():
4745                        beh_ind = int(split[-1])
4746                        metric_name = "_".join(split[:-1])
4747                        beh = beh_dict[beh_ind]
4748                    else:
4749                        beh = "average"
4750                        metric_name = column[1]
4751                    res_dict[beh][metric_name] = episodes.loc[run, column]
4752                    metric_set.add(metric_name)
4753                if "average" not in res_dict:
4754                    res_dict["average"] = {}
4755                for metric in metric_set:
4756                    if metric not in res_dict["average"]:
4757                        arr = [
4758                            res_dict[beh][metric]
4759                            for beh in res_dict
4760                            if metric in res_dict[beh]
4761                        ]
4762                        res_dict["average"][metric] = np.mean(arr)
4763                results.append(res_dict)
4764            episode_results = {}
4765            for metric in metric_set:
4766                for beh in results[0].keys():
4767                    if classes is not None and beh not in classes:
4768                        continue
4769                    arr = []
4770                    for res_dict in results:
4771                        if metric in res_dict[beh]:
4772                            arr.append(res_dict[beh][metric])
4773                    if len(arr) > 0:
4774                        if include_std:
4775                            episode_results[
4776                                (beh, f"{episode} {metric} mean")
4777                            ] = np.mean(arr)
4778                            episode_results[(beh, f"{episode} {metric} std")] = np.std(
4779                                arr
4780                            )
4781                        else:
4782                            episode_results[(beh, f"{episode} {metric}")] = np.mean(arr)
4783            for key, value in episode_results.items():
4784                results_df.loc[key[0], key[1]] = value
4785        print(f"RESULTS:")
4786        print(results_df)
4787        print("\n")
4788        return results_df
4789

A class to create and maintain the project files + keep track of experiments

Project( name: str, data_type: str = None, annotation_type: str = 'none', projects_path: str = None, data_path: Union[str, List] = None, annotation_path: Union[str, List] = None, copy: bool = False) 
 56    def __init__(
 57        self,
 58        name: str,
 59        data_type: str = None,
 60        annotation_type: str = "none",
 61        projects_path: str = None,
 62        data_path: Union[str, List] = None,
 63        annotation_path: Union[str, List] = None,
 64        copy: bool = False,
 65    ) -> None:
 66        """
 67        Parameters
 68        ----------
 69        name : str
 70            name of the project
 71        data_type : str, optional
 72            data type (run Project.data_types() to see available options; has to be provided if the project is being
 73            created)
 74        annotation_type : str, default 'none'
 75            annotation type (run Project.annotation_types() to see available options)
 76        projects_path : str, optional
 77            path to the projects folder (is filled with ~/DLC2Action by default)
 78        data_path : str, optional
 79            path to the folder containing input files for the project (has to be provided if the project is being
 80            created)
 81        annotation_path : str, optional
 82            path to the folder containing annotation files for the project
 83        copy : bool, default False
 84            if True, the files from annotation_path and data_path will be copied to the projects folder;
 85            otherwise they will be moved
 86        """
 87
 88        if projects_path is None:
 89            projects_path = os.path.join(str(Path.home()), "DLC2Action")
 90        if not os.path.exists(projects_path):
 91            os.mkdir(projects_path)
 92        self.project_path = os.path.join(projects_path, name)
 93        self.name = name
 94        self.data_type = data_type
 95        self.annotation_type = annotation_type
 96        self.data_path = data_path
 97        self.annotation_path = annotation_path
 98        if not os.path.exists(self.project_path):
 99            if data_type is None:
100                raise ValueError(
101                    "The data_type parameter is necessary when creating a new project!"
102                )
103            self._initialize_project(
104                data_type, annotation_type, data_path, annotation_path, copy
105            )
106        else:
107            self.annotation_type, self.data_type = self._read_types()
108            if data_type != self.data_type and data_type is not None:
109                raise ValueError(
110                    f"The project has already been initialized with data_type={self.data_type}!"
111                )
112            if annotation_type != self.annotation_type and annotation_type != "none":
113                raise ValueError(
114                    f"The project has already been initialized with annotation_type={self.annotation_type}!"
115                )
116            self.annotation_path, data_path = self._read_paths()
117            if self.data_path is None:
118                self.data_path = data_path
119            # if data_path != self.data_path and data_path is not None:
120            #     raise ValueError(
121            #         f"The project has already been initialized with data_path={self.data_path}!"
122            #     )
123            if annotation_path != self.annotation_path and annotation_path is not None:
124                raise ValueError(
125                    f"The project has already been initialized with annotation_path={self.annotation_path}!"
126                )
127        self._update_configs()
