4688            )

Save selected episodes as a file that can be imported into another project with Project.import_episodes

def get_results_table( self, episode_names: List, metrics: List = None, include_std: bool = False, classes: List = None) 
4696    def get_results_table(
4697        self,
4698        episode_names: List,
4699        metrics: List = None,
4700        include_std: bool = False,
4701        classes: List = None,
4702    ):
4703        """
4704        Genererate a `pandas` dataframe with a summary of episode results
4705
4706        Parameters
4707        ----------
4708        episode_names : list
4709            a list of names of episodes to include
4710        metrics : list, optional
4711            a list of metric names to include
4712        include_std : bool, default False
4713            if `True`, for episodes with multiple runs the mean and standard deviation will be displayed;
4714            otherwise only mean
4715        classes : list, optional
4716            a list of names of classes to include (by default all are included)
4717
4718        Returns
4719        -------
4720        results : pd.DataFrame
4721            a table with the results
4722        """
4723
4724        run_names = []
4725        for episode in episode_names:
4726            run_names += self._episodes().get_runs(episode)
4727        episodes = self.list_episodes(run_names, print_results=False)
4728        metric_columns = [x for x in episodes.columns if x[0] == "results"]
4729        results_df = pd.DataFrame()
4730        if metrics is not None:
4731            metric_columns = [
4732                x for x in metric_columns if x[1].split("_")[0] in metrics
4733            ]
4734        for episode in episode_names:
4735            results = []
4736            metric_set = set()
4737            for run in self._episodes().get_runs(episode):
4738                beh_dict = self.get_behavior_dictionary(run)
4739                res_dict = defaultdict(lambda: {})
4740                for column in metric_columns:
4741                    if np.isnan(episodes.loc[run, column]):
4742                        continue
4743                    split = column[1].split("_")
4744                    if split[-1].isnumeric():
4745                        beh_ind = int(split[-1])
4746                        metric_name = "_".join(split[:-1])
4747                        beh = beh_dict[beh_ind]
4748                    else:
4749                        beh = "average"
4750                        metric_name = column[1]
4751                    res_dict[beh][metric_name] = episodes.loc[run, column]
4752                    metric_set.add(metric_name)
4753                if "average" not in res_dict:
4754                    res_dict["average"] = {}
4755                for metric in metric_set:
4756                    if metric not in res_dict["average"]:
4757                        arr = [
4758                            res_dict[beh][metric]
4759                            for beh in res_dict
4760                            if metric in res_dict[beh]
4761                        ]
4762                        res_dict["average"][metric] = np.mean(arr)
4763                results.append(res_dict)
4764            episode_results = {}
4765            for metric in metric_set:
4766                for beh in results[0].keys():
4767                    if classes is not None and beh not in classes:
4768                        continue
4769                    arr = []
4770                    for res_dict in results:
4771                        if metric in res_dict[beh]:
4772                            arr.append(res_dict[beh][metric])
4773                    if len(arr) > 0:
4774                        if include_std:
4775                            episode_results[
4776                                (beh, f"{episode} {metric} mean")
4777                            ] = np.mean(arr)
4778                            episode_results[(beh, f"{episode} {metric} std")] = np.std(
4779                                arr
4780                            )
4781                        else:
4782                            episode_results[(beh, f"{episode} {metric}")] = np.mean(arr)
4783            for key, value in episode_results.items():
4784                results_df.loc[key[0], key[1]] = value
4785        print(f"RESULTS:")
4786        print(results_df)
4787        print("\n")
4788        return results_df

Returns

results : pd.DataFrame a table with the results
